    • Method Detail

      • list

        Interfaces.ListInvocation list(java.lang.String vm)
        Returns information about the networking interfaces in the guest operating system. This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

        Invocation Result:
        Information about the interfaces configured in the guest operating system. Interfaces are ordered in a guest operating system specific determined order.

        Parameters:
        vm - Virtual machine ID The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: VirtualMachine.
        Returns:
        instance of Interfaces.ListInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described list operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        Error - if the system reports an error while responding to the request.
        NotFound - if the virtual machine is not found.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        ServiceUnavailable - if VMware Tools is not running.
